26 LC 112 4309
House Resolution 19EX
By: Representatives Okoye of the 102nd, McQueen of the 61st, McClain of the 109th, Adeyina
of the 110th, and Beckles of the 96th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Debrah Georges; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Debrah Georges is an Antiguan American community leader, civic advocate,
3 and public servant whose dedication to service has positively impacted communities
4 throughout Georgia for more than two decades; and
5 WHEREAS, Debrah Georges has devoted her life to strengthening communities through
6 civic engagement, cultural preservation, volunteerism, and leadership; serving as a consistent
7 advocate for increasing community participation in the democratic process; and creating
8 opportunities for diverse voices to be heard and represented; and
9 WHEREAS, throughout her years of service, she has held leadership positions within
10 numerous community and civic organizations, helping to advance initiatives focused on
11 education, voter engagement, cultural awareness, and community development; and
12 WHEREAS, her commitment to public service has extended to grassroots organizing,
13 political engagement, and community outreach efforts that have helped empower individuals
14 and strengthen neighborhoods across Georgia; and
H. R. 19EX
- 1 -

26 LC 112 4309
15 WHEREAS, in addition to her community work, Debrah has built a distinguished
16 professional career spanning the financial services, banking, technology, healthcare, and
17 government sectors; and
18 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentlewoman has given inspiration to many through her high
19 ideals, morals, and deep concern for her fellow citizens, and she possesses the vast wisdom
20 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
21 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
22 WHEREAS, she is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
23 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
25 remarkable and distinguished individual be appropriately honored.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend Debrah Georges for her outstanding
28 contributions to the community, her commitment to public service, and her lasting impact
29 on the lives of countless individuals and families throughout Georgia.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Debrah Georges.
